<br>
-TELEK  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">*Zannah*<br>
<br>
Zannah is obviously the best Magi in this deck.  What I like to do is get one creature out there and pump it up FAST.  That way whenever your opponent want&#39;s to attack, they have to sacrifice a creature.  If you get it big enough, they will probably have to use all of their creatures, and your creature will stay alive.  Pumping up creatures is pretty easy if you get a Pruitt&#39;s Robe and a Dream Channel.  And you can use your spells to stall until you get one.<br>
<br>
*Pruitt*<br>
<br>
Pruitt isn&#39;t exactly the best magi in this deck, but works good to set up for Sperri.  Since you used a lot of your cards with Zannah, you need to save some good cards so you have some combos for Sperri to start with.  With Pruitt the best thing to do is swarm.  If you have creatures left over from Zannah, play as much as you can.  You should also get your Pruitt&#39;s robe and Robe of vines out there.  That way you can swarm with lot&#39;s of low-energy creatures, and have them turn into high level creatures before your eyes.  It would be a good idea to save all of your Furoks for Sperri.<br>
<br>
*Sperri*<br>
<br>
With Sperri, you can do pretty good by getting a Robe of Vines and Pruitt&#39;s Robe out on the first turn (like every magi in this deck...).  You should also have three Furoks and one Furok Guardian in your hand, and you should play them all ASAP.  With the Robe of Vines and Sperri&#39;s effect, that means 7 energy Furoks, and 13 energy Furok Guardians.<br>
<br>
<br>
Universal Combos:<br>
<br>
Giant Carillion + Pruitt&#39;s Robe: use this whenever you can.  Works REALLY good.<br>
<br>
Why This Deck Is Fun:  Zannah + Pruitt&#39;s Robe + 3 Dream Channels + Giant Carillion + Robe of Vines... BWAHAHAHAHAHA! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
